<div id="Story3" style="padding:0 12px;box-sizing:border-box;">
                <div class="section_heading" style="width:100%; background-color: transparent;box-sizing:border-box;padding-bottom:12px;">
                    <div id="web3" style="width:100%;max-width:115px;height:1px;background-color:#D3D3D3;margin:24px auto; ">
                    </div>
                    <h3 style="padding:0;width:100%;font-family:Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-weight:700;font-size:16px;color:#93888F;line-height:23.1px;text-align: left;margin:0;text-transform:uppercase;">Fintech</h3>
                </div>
                <div style="width:100%; background-color: transparent; box-sizing:border-box;">
                    <h3 style="width:100%; font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:16px;margin:0;padding-bottom:16px;font-weight:700;color:#28121F;line-height:20px;text-transform:capitalize;letter-spacing:-0.32px;text-align:left;box-sizing:border-box;">Egypt&#8217;s largest commercial bank invests in fintech MNT-Halan in a round valuing it at $1.4 billion</h3>
                    <div style="font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;padding-bottom:16px;box-sizing:border-box;">
<figure style="width: 100%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:left;margin:0">


                        <a href="https://techcabal.com/category/newsletters/tc-daily/">
                             <img decoding="async" 
     	loading="lazy" src="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/06/4H4ZDS3T2NPQHJICM3FWIYFNPQ.avif" width="100%" height="auto" style="object-fit: cover"></a>
                         <figcaption style="color:#808080;font-size:12px;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;line-height:19.8px;padding-top:6px;font-weight:400">Mounir Nakhla, co-founder of Egyptian fintech companies MNT and Halan is seen during an interview with Reuters in Cairo, Egypt June 22, 2021. Image Source: Reuters</figcaption>
                    </figure>
                        
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;">A state-owned commercial bank just invested in a fintech unicorn. That&#8217;s not something you see every day.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;">In a <a href="https://ent.news/2026/6/508.pdf" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #b61313 !important;">statement on Monday</a>, MNT-Halan, the Egyptian-founded fintech that <a href="https://qz.com/egypts-mnt-halan-is-africas-newest-unicorn-1850081583" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #b61313 !important;">became a unicorn in 2023</a>, said it secured an undisclosed investment from Al Ahly Capital, the investment arm of the National Bank of Egypt (NBE)</a>, Egypt&#8217;s largest state-owned commercial bank. The deal lifts MNT-Halan&#8217;s valuation to $1.4 billion and marks the first closing of a broader funding round.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;">MNT-Halan, founded in 2018, lends to small businesses and consumers who struggle to access traditional bank credit. It also offers e-wallets, prepaid cards, and financing products through its Halan app. Since its launch, the company says it has <a href="https://ent.news/2026/6/508.pdf" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #b61313 !important;">disbursed over $15.5 billion in loans</a> and served over 8 million customers across Egypt, T&uuml;rkiye, Pakistan, and the United Arab Emirates (UAE).</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;"><strong>State of play: </strong>With the new funding, MNT Halan said it plans to deepen its presence in Egypt and continue its expansion into new markets in the Gulf region.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;"><strong>Why did NBE directly back a fintech? </strong>The investment stands out because of who is making it. NBE has <a href="https://fintech-egypt.com/news/news_details.php?id=153" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #b61313 !important;">backed Egypt&#8217;s fintech sector before</a>, but mostly through investment vehicles such as Nclude, a fintech-focused venture fund launched in 2022. Direct equity investments into individual startups have been far less common.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;">More importantly, MNT-Halan has spent years building partnerships with more than 30 Egyptian banks. Yet no commercial bank had previously taken an ownership stake in the company. Founder Mounir Nakhla called the transaction a &ldquo;particularly important milestone&rdquo; because it marks the first time a bank has become an equity partner in the fintech&#8217;s journey.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;"><strong>The shift says something about the state of Egypt&#8217;s fintech market.</strong> A few years ago, banks viewed fintechs as challengers nibbling at parts of their business. Today, Egypt&#8217;s largest bank appears willing to treat them as partners, distribution channels, and investment opportunities.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;margin:0;">International investors helped prove that MNT-Halan could become a billion-dollar company. NBE&#8217;s investment signals something different: Egypt&#8217;s traditional financial establishment now believes fintech is a sector worth owning, not merely watching.</p>
</div>
